{
  "text": "for C145S-AGT, agree well with values found for short, unmodified dsDNAs, under similar conditions [CITATION_1] , and are 2-4 fold larger than affinities measured for linear and relaxed-circular pUC19 DNAs (2686 bp), under similar buffer conditions [CITATION_2] . Thus, they are fair representations of the lesion-non-specific interaction of AGT with duplex DNA.",
